			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Andrew, you've got it all wrong. First of all, Fire Elementals are excellent. They have the quickest attack, and when you get these higher level elems that can double attack, bash, and cast a spell at the same time, then wait barely a second before doing it again, you'll see how much fun these are. Also, they're great for clearing away the smaller creatures that like to annoy you, blue or green con's that are very aggresive. Weaker creatures fall to a Fire Elemental before I have chance to hit them.And yes, they do have less HP, but that's not too bad because the monsters just can't do as much damage to it as they can an Earth Elemental or something because it takes them down so fast. Also, Earth Elementals do have some agility.. I had an Earth Elementaling that conned yellow to me at 8, and I attacked a skeleton that also conned yellow (in Steamfont). Well, as usual I blasted it and then had my pet do the intercept thing, and the skel attacked and MISSED 4 TIMES IN A ROW! It hit and hit and missed missed missed missed missed hit and then it was dead. My elemental still had 86 percent of his hit points remaining! That never happened to me before, so maybe Earth Elems got their Agility upped in that last patch...
				</font>
			</td>

